    <h2>Understanding the Freight Management System</h2>
      <p>Our Freight Management System is designed to streamline the management of freight, connecting Controllers, Drivers, and Shippers seamlessly. By enhancing communication and reducing errors, it significantly improves efficiency in freight logistics.</p>

    <h2>Diverse User Functionalities</h2>
<p>Our system offers diverse functionalities tailored to three main user roles: Controllers, Drivers, and Shippers. Let's explore what each of these users can achieve using our system:</p>

<h3>Controllers</h3>
<p>Controllers are the backbone of our Freight Management System. They play a critical role in coordinating and managing the entire logistics network. With our system, Controllers can:</p>
<ul>
    <li>Efficiently allocate loads to available Drivers based on various parameters, such as location, vehicle capacity, and delivery timeframes.</li>
    <li>Monitor the progress of loads in real-time, allowing them to make informed decisions and adapt to unforeseen circumstances.</li>
    <li>Receive incident reports and damage notifications, enabling quick responses to address issues that may arise during transport.</li>
</ul>

<h3>Drivers</h3>
<p>Drivers are the front-line workers who ensure that shipments are transported safely and on time. Our system empowers Drivers with tools to enhance their efficiency and communication. With our system, Drivers can:</p>
<ul>
    <li>Access load information, including departure and destination details, goods in transit, and any specific instructions or requirements.</li>
    <li>Report incidents and damages, providing essential information to Controllers and Shippers to address issues promptly.</li>
    <li>Update their personal information, such as contact details and passwords, to maintain accurate records.</li>
</ul>

<h3>Shippers</h3>
<p>Shippers are responsible for initiating shipments and ensuring their goods reach the intended destination. Our system simplifies this process for Shippers. With our system, Shippers can:</p>
<ul>
    <li>Initiate load requests, providing detailed information about the shipment, including goods description, collection and drop-off locations, and preferred delivery times.</li>
    <li>Receive real-time updates on their shipments' status, ensuring they have visibility and control over the transportation process.</li>
    <li>Report damages and incidents related to their shipments, allowing for prompt resolution and claims processing.</li>
</ul>
